description.narrative:
Broad objective: Strengthen the role of Community Based Organizations to contribute to improving the quality of health and educational service delivery and infrastructural projects in Grand Bassa County.

Specific objectives: 

1)	To organize refresher training for two CBOs in Grand Bassa that partnered in the first phase of the project, members of the Project Management Committee  (PMC) and select staff from at least 6 member organizations of the CSO Platform on Decentralization on the Community Integrity Building approach and tools such as CRC for monitoring and advocacy and the use of DevelopmentCheck for reporting;  

2)	To monitor 8 public health and educational facilities (4 elementary, junior high and 4 health care facilities)  to be jointly identified at the community forum and follow up on previous projects monitored last year to ensure unresolved problems are addressed;

3)	To advocate (local and national level) for improved health and educational services at the public facilities to be monitored by ensuring that problems are resolved and services impacts and improves the lives of the poor the most.;
